# mcp-vertex Cursor Rules

Always refer to the canonical onboarding and workflow rules before performing any work in this repository:
- Read [AGENTS.md](file:///home/cartago/_projects/mcp-vertex/AGENTS.md) first for monorepo invariants, commands, and conventions.
- Refer to [docs/scaffolds/ARCHITECTURE-PROPOSALS.md](file:///home/cartago/_projects/mcp-vertex/docs/scaffolds/ARCHITECTURE-PROPOSALS.md) when working with proposals.
- Refer to [docs/scaffolds/ARCHITECTURE-AUDITS.md](file:///home/cartago/_projects/mcp-vertex/docs/scaffolds/ARCHITECTURE-AUDITS.md) when creating/modifying audits.

## Audits & Proposals Filename Conventions

Every audit proposal must follow the exact chronological name structure:
`docs/proposals/ready/{numAuditoria}-{DD}-{MM}-{YYYY}-{controladorModelo}-{modelo}-{queSeHaAuditado}.md` (if pending tasks remain) or
`docs/proposals/done/audits/{numAuditoria}-{DD}-{MM}-{YYYY}-{controladorModelo}-{modelo}-{queSeHaAuditado}.md` (if all tasks are completed or deferred)

Where:
- `numAuditoria` is the chronological identifier (e.g., `a021`).
- `DD`, `MM`, `YYYY` is the day, month, and 4-digit year (e.g., `21-06-2026`).
- `controladorModelo` is the client/runner driving the model (e.g., `antigravity`, `claude-code`, `codex`, `copilot`).
- `modelo` is the AI model (e.g., `gemini-3-5-flash`, `opus-4-8`, `gpt-5-5`).
- `queSeHaAuditado` describes the audited scope (e.g., `repositorio`, `plugins`, `apps`, `web`, `extensionvscode`).
